HEADWORD: Teste
<hw>Tes"te</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[So called fr. L.
<ets>teste</ets>, abl. of <ets>testis</ets> a witness, because this was
formerly the initial word in the clause.]</ety> <fld>(Law)</fld>
<sd>(a)</sd> <def>A witness.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>The witnessing or
concluding clause, duty attached; -- said of a writ, deed, or the
like.</def> <rj><au>Burrill.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tester</ent>⟦br⟧
